Having a meal at the Coconut Palm Restaurant always reminds me of eating a home cook Guyanese meal. The food is always fresh & tasty. During this pandemic they're doing a great job with mask wearing, social distancing & sanitizing. The outdoor area in the back yard is very comfortable I felt very safe having my dinner. The tables are spread apart, all the employees are wearing their mask & they have a sanitizer station for guest.  Always a pleasure visiting this restaurant.

Personally one of my favorite spots for Caribbean / Guyanese-Chinese food. It's your standard fare of lo mein, fried rice, and a variety of other food items, but also has a great selection of Curry and food items for large get-togethers. The one reason that I don't give the place 5 stars is due to the slow service that you can encounter at times. The bartender's are more focused on drinking patrons at the bar rather than food for takeout, and sometimes that is very apparent in the way that you are greeted or the speed at which you are addressed. I get that they are probably trolling for tips, but even prior to the pandemic, there was a need for improvement in this particular area. Call ahead, give them like 40 minutes (even when they say 15-20) to prepare your food, and hopefully it will be waiting for you at the bar when you walk in.
